messages.message:
Hi! This is a tutorial showing you how to use the interface. You will go through the following things:
1. how to annotate incoming messages
2. how to submit beginning-of-phase moves
3. how to send a lie
4. how to change status to ready when you are ready to proceed to the next turn
Should you have any questions, send an email to fgu1@umd.edu
Now, the first thing you will notice is that you can only see this message. But the counter indicates that there are more. Click the button below this message to indicate this is not a lie and to see the next message.

Congratulations! you conpleted 1. Now, you will notice that your textbox is disabled and you cannot send message to other powers. Before you can send messages to other powers, you will need to 1)set your stance toward other powers on lower right. 2)set orders for all your units as if no communication happened at all this round. You can see all the units you need to set orders for on upper right "Orderable locations".
How to create order:
On upper right, select the type of order you want to create: move/support/hold. Then click on the map.
For move orders: click the unit, then the destination. The interface will prompt you if a convoy is available.
For support orders: click the unit, then the unit you want to support, then destination
For hold: click unit.
Now you will notice the textbox is enabled. Annotate this message to proceed to the next step.

To send a message, enter the message in the textbox, then select one of the following:
truth: if you are telling a truth
lie: if you are telling a lie
neutral: if you are asking a question, greeting, etc.
Annotate this message to proceed to the next step.

Above all your set orders on the right, you will see a status (ready/not ready). If you finalized your orders and communication, make sure the status is a green ready. If all powers are ready, the game will immediately proceed to the next phase, and the deadline will reset. This is to ensure we don't spend too much time on retreat/adjustment phases. Annotate this message to proceed to the next step.

Other interface information:
You can see how much time is left for this turn on the top left
the reset button next to orders means remove all unsaved orders (whereas the reset button next to the create order types means cancel building the current order). Saved orders will have a [S] next to it.
Please exit the tutorial by clicking username-> leave game on the top right corner and join the game (details in your email) when you finish.
